irective</a> - European rules on applicable fees for late payments.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-18T10:16:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-billing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Payments</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=20043944\">High failure rate of Point Of Sale devices in the upper Midwest</a> - The root cause? People wearing a lot of wool in low humidity air, generating a lot of static.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-18T10:16:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-billing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Payments</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>How ACH works: A developer perspective, <a href=\"https://engineering.gusto.com/how-ach-works-a-developer-perspective-part-1/\">part 1</a>, <a href=\"https://engineering.gusto.com/how-ach-works-a-developer-perspective-part-2/\">part 2</a>, <a href=\"https://engineering.gusto.com/how-ach-works-a-developer-perspective-part-3/\">part 3</a>, <a href=\"https://engineering.gusto.com/how-ach-works-a-developer-perspective-part-4/\">part 4</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-18T10:16:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-billing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Payments</h2><h3>Receipt</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.fastcompany.com/90347782/the-humble-receipt-gets-a-brilliant-redesign\">The humble receipt gets a brilliant redesign</a> - When a Netflix data engineer revisit receipts.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-18T10:16:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-billing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Payments</h2><h3>Credit Cards</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cbc.ca/news/business/banking-information-shared-with-third-parties-1.5102931\">'Is that even legal?': Companies may be sharing new credit or debit card information without you knowing</a> - Some credit and debit card companies have \"updating service\" that allows new account numbers and expiry dates to be shared with merchants. Visa's implementation is called <a href=\"https://developer.visa.com/capabilities/vau\">VAU</a> and Mastercard's is <a href=\"https://developer.mastercard.com/product/automatic-billing-updater\">ABU</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-18T10:16:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-billing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Payments</h2><h3>Credit Cards</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://stripe.com/guides/strong-customer-authentication\">Strong Customer Authentication</a> - <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Payment_Services_Directive\">Payment Services Directive</a> 2, explained.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-18T10:16:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-billing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Payments</h2><h3>Credit Cards</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Address_Verification_System\">Address Verification System</a> - A system checking the matching of customer's billing addresses with the one associated with the credit card.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-18T10:16:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-billing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Fraud</h2><h3>Cards</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.candyjapan.com/behind-the-scenes/how-i-got-credit-card-fraud-somewhat-under-control\">How Candy Japan got credit card fraud somewhat under control</a> - Suggestions involved either <a href=\"https://www.candyjapan.com/behind-the-scenes/fraudulent-transaction-warning-signs\">warning signals</a> for trying to guess which orders might be fraud, or countermeasures to try to make things harder for the fraudsters.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-18T10:16:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-billing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Fraud</h2><h3>Cards</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://blog.sift.com/2013/five-ecommerce-fraud-facts/\">Five Fun Fraud Facts</a> - Another tiny collection of features we can feed to a ML system to detect fraud. Comments on HN also unearthed <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=6376350\">more qualifying signals</a> and <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=6376221\">derived geodata on the transaction</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-18T10:16:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-billing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Fraud</h2><h3>Cards</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/@curiousily/credit-card-fraud-detection-using-autoencoders-in-keras-tensorflow-for-hackers-part-vii-20e0c85301bd\">Credit Card Fraud Detection using Autoencoders in Keras</a> - Tutorial on how to rely on anomaly detection to implement suspicious card transactions.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-18T10:16:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-billing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Fraud</h2><h3>Trust Score</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://cloudplatform.googleblog.com/2018/07/improving-our-account-management-policies-to-better-support-customers.html\">GCP improved account management policies to better support customers</a> - Or why relying too much on fraud automation might lead to disgruntled users.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-18T10:16:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-billing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Fraud</h2><h3>Billing</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.knowbe4.com/ceo-fraud\">CEO Fraud</a> - A billing team responsible for collecting payment is prey to this kind of fraud, in which the CEO is impersonated to commend exceptional payment transactions.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-18T10:16:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-billing","categoryHTML":"<h2>UX/UI</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/subscriptions/overview/\">Apple Subscriptions HIG</a> - Guide and recommendation on how to make <a href=\"https://developer.apple.com/app-store/subscriptions/\">auto-renewable subscriptions</a> user-friendly.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-18T10:16:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-billing","categoryHTML":"<h2>UX/UI</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://capitalandgrowth.org/questions/2055/which-has-a-higher-conversion-rate-a-single-long-e.html\">Which has a higher conversion rate: A single long ecommerce checkout form or a multi-step one?</a> - Focus first on other things in the cart, like easing anxiety and second-guessing by adding reassurance (trust marks, testimonials) near the credit card and completion steps, as well as some guarantee language that you may have used earlier in the product exploration process.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-18T10:16:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-billing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Competitive Analysis</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/grosskur/ec2price\">EC2 Spot Price Tracker</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/grosskur/ec2price\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">125</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":125,\"repo\":\"grosskur/ec2price\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Web app that collects and graphs EC2 Spot Prices.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-18T10:16:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-billing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Competitive Analysis</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.gcpweekly.com/gcp-resources/tag/billing/\">GCP billing news</a> - From the unofficial Google Cloud Platform newsletter.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-18T10:16:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"meirwah/awesome-incident-response","categoryHTML":"<h2>IR Tools Collection</h2><h3>Communities</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://dfircommunity.slack.com\">Slack DFIR channel</a> - Slack DFIR Communitiy channel - <a href=\"https://start.paloaltonetworks.com/join-our-slack-community\">Signup here</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"20